  "prompt": "How do you know if a guy is obsessed with you?",
  "response": "Identifying if someone is obsessed with you involves observing their behavior and noting any signs that may suggest an unhealthy level of interest. Here are some indicators that a guy might be obsessed:\n\n1. **Constant Communication**: He texts, calls, or messages you incessantly, expecting immediate responses and becoming upset if you don't reply quickly.\n\n2. **Excessive Attention**: He pays you an overwhelming amount of attention, wanting to be involved in every aspect of your life, including showing up unexpectedly in places you frequent.\n\n3. **Jealousy and Possessiveness**: He becomes overly jealous when you interact with others, trying to monopolize your time and showing signs of possessiveness.\n\n4. **Stalking Behavior**: He follows you on social media obsessively, monitors your activities, and possibly shows up at locations without your invitation.\n\n5. **Ignoring Boundaries**: He disregards your personal boundaries, insisting on spending time together even when you\u2019ve expressed the need for space.\n\n6. **Quick Escalation**: He moves too quickly in the relationship, pushing for deep commitment early on without considering your comfort or readiness.\n\n7. **Overreacting to Rejection**: He responds poorly to any form of rejection or cancellation, reacting with anger, guilt-tripping, or excessive emotional displays.\n\n8. **Idolization**: He places you on a pedestal, seeing you as perfect to a point where it seems unrealistic.\n\n9. **Neglects Other Relationships**: He neglects his friends, family, or personal interests to spend all his time and energy on you.\n\n10. **Emotional Manipulation**: He might use guilt, fear, or manipulation to keep you close or to get his way.\n\nIf you notice these behaviors, it's important to evaluate the situation carefully. Consider seeking advice or discussing it with someone you trust, and if necessary, establish clear boundaries or involve professional help like a counselor or therapist.",
